args: Whew! It took longer than I expected,\nbut that's the last of the fiends.
There were loads of 'em, all right.\nYou gotta be tired after all the runnin'\naround ya been doin' lately.
Oh, I'm fine. Just seeing the looks of relief\non everyone's faces is enough to make my\nexhaustion fade away.
Bwa ha ha! That's our prince!
Training again today, Your Highness?\nWould you care to spar with me?
Getting the warehouse in order must take a\nlot of effort, Cleo. Let me give you a hand.
Could you carry this for me, then?
This? Hnnngggh! Oh wow,\nthis is seriously heavy.
Would you let me read your fortune today?\nThere's something I have been wondering\nabout.
Oh, please don't be like that.\nIt won't take long.
Thank you. I'll start right away.\nHmm...
What is it? What did you see?
I apologize for losing my composure.\nBut the future I saw was most ominous.
You are in a most perilous position at the\nmoment. If you don't do something, I fear\na great misfortune will descend upon you.
Will you leave this to me? I will see if\nI can avert it and change your future.
All right. I appreciate it, Verica.
I will not disappoint you. Now then,\nif you would come right this way?
Good. Lie down and rest your head here.
It's not that—it's just... Well, I suppose\nthis is no time for being embarrassed.
So if this is really what I have to do...
Heh. It is, I promise you.
A-all right, I've got my head down.\nWhat should I do next?
Let us not get ahead of ourselves.\nJust take it nice and easy...\nBreathe slowly and deeply...
Right, then. I'll just breathe...\nBreathe... Breeeeeatheeee...
H-huh?! Oh, sorry! I think I drifted off for a\nmoment there.
You are quite welcome to keep napping\nif you wish it.
Or perhaps I should sing you a lullaby so\nyou can have a proper sleep?
Er, that's okay. But what happened to\nchanging my destiny?
Heh. That was, I fear, a lie.
I did not look into your future today.
Then what has all this been about?!
While what I said about your future being\nominous wasn't exactly true, the part about\nyou being in a dangerous position was.
At this rate, a great misfortune will\ndescend upon you ere long.
I'm going to need you to explain that.

You are greatly overworking yourself.
Day in and day out, you fight fiends,
train, and take care of other assorted
tasks around the castle.
No one can handle so much work\nindefinitely. You must rest.
I think you're worrying too much.\nI'm pretty much the picture of health.
Someone who was the picture of health\nwould not fall asleep the second they\nlie down.
If you were to collapse from overwork,\nit would be the people around you who\nwould suffer the most.
When you have the chance to rest, you\nneed to do so. You have a DUTY to do so.
Good. Then it's time for sleep.
I have a duty to watch over you until the\nmoment you finally surrender to slumber.\nNow close your eyes.

♪ Sleep, oh sleep, my dearest child,
and may your dreams be soft and mild.
Then on the morrow you'll awake,
at the moment of dawn's break. ♪
